annotationA: GH05218p; Aldehyde dehydrogenase (NAD) activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: oxidation-reduction process
annotationB: Alcohol dehydrogenase class-3; Class-III ADH is remarkably ineffective in oxidizing ethanol, but it readily catalyzes the oxidation of long-chain primary alcohols and the oxidation of S-(hydroxymethyl) glutathione; Belongs to the zinc-containing alcohol dehydrogenase family.
